+# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260326-223118-f62f
+
+## Findings
+1. [P2] Current-visit filtering is not implemented — `CartView` still renders submitted history from `myOrders` directly in the drawer (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:664-690`), while `x.jsx` passes both `myOrders` and `sessionOrders` into the component (`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3555-3563`). There is no `created_date`, `toDateString()`, or current-session filter anywhere in `CartView.jsx`, so the PM-142 "today/current session only" rule is still missing. FIX: derive a `currentVisitOrders` subset from `myOrders`/`sessionOrders` using today's date or the active session id, then render only that subset.
+2. [P2] Required newest-first full-datetime ordering is missing — the drawer maps orders in incoming order with no local sort (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:690-760`), and the only time helper shown in the UI formats HH:MM only (`pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:1241-1247`). That means the PM-143 requirement to order by full datetime is not implemented in this target file. FIX: sort each rendered order group by `new Date(order.created_at || order.created_date || order.createdAt).getTime()` descending before rendering.
+3. [P2] The agreed `Выдано` / `Заказано` structure is absent — current code keeps one `myOrdersExpanded` toggle and one combined "Ваши заказы" section with a separate section total `myBill.total` in the header (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:663-689`). The spec requires two status-based sections with different default expansion states and no separate per-section totals. FIX: split current-visit orders into served vs active groups by item statuses, add separate expand/collapse state for each group, and remove the header-level `myBill.total`.
+4. [P2] `Новый заказ` can still be buried below history — the cart section is rendered only after the full submitted-orders block (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:663-790` then `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:793-918`). Because all prior orders stay ahead of it in one accordion, the user can still need to scroll through history before reaching the steppers, which keeps PM-144 unresolved. FIX: keep history grouped/collapsed per spec and render `Новый заказ` as its own always-visible top-level section before the visit-total/CTA block.
+5. [P2] The single `ИТОГО за визит` total and PM-145 rounding fix are missing — the only visible total in the drawer is cart-only `cartTotalAmount` (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:906-913`), while submitted-order amounts use raw `item.line_total` / `order.total_amount` (`pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:717`, `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:755`). There is no combined visit total across served + active + draft items, and no `parseFloat(total.toFixed(2))` normalization in `CartView.jsx`. FIX: compute one `visitTotal` from all current-visit submitted items plus current cart, normalize it with `parseFloat(visitTotal.toFixed(2))`, and use the same normalization for displayed order subtotals.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 5 P2, 0 P3)
+
+## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
+- Overall clarity: 3
+- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 itself was detailed; no major ambiguity inside the UX rules.
+- Missing context (what info would have helped): The prompt references `BUGS_MASTER.md`, but that file was not present at the repo root, and the instructions also said not to read outside the page folder. It also was not explicit whether `myOrders` is already filtered upstream, so the review had to judge the target file as-is.
+- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): The speed rule forbids reading files outside the page folder, but the TASK CONTEXT explicitly names `BUGS_MASTER.md` outside that folder. The task also labels `CartView.jsx` as a file to "modify" even though this pipeline step asked for review-only output.
